OL,3,CRetreat owner threw chemical at
OL,4,Cguest's face before fleeing the country
OL,6,FHe had blisters on his body for about
OL,7,Fa month, some of which have left
OL,8,Flifelong scars, Mr Taylor said. He was
OL,9,Fsegregated from other prisoners and
OL,10,Fconfined to a cell to prevent a larger
OL,11,Fbreakout, Mr Taylor said.
OL,13,FThe barrister added: "The punishment
OL,14,Fhe received abroad was far more
OL,15,Fserious than anything he could receive
OL,16,Fin the UK. Conditions in Romania
OL,17,Fshocked him to his core and were far
OL,18,Fmore difficult than anything he's
OL,19,Fencountered in this country."
